through a wormhole to Mars.

00:02:06.880 --> 00:02:09.100 align:middle line:84%
So the whole trip
took a few minutes.

00:02:09.100 --> 00:02:12.550 align:middle line:84%
And then we landed on the
tarmac at Ares Primis, which

00:02:12.550 --> 00:02:16.540 align:middle line:84%
was the military headquarters
corporate headquarters

00:02:16.540 --> 00:02:18.010 align:middle line:90%
of the Mars colonies.

00:02:18.010 --> 00:02:21.870 align:middle line:84%
And then I was sent to a forward
station far, far north, What.

00:02:21.870 --> 00:02:25.630 align:middle line:84%
I sort of refer to
as "Alaska region."

00:02:25.630 --> 00:02:31.990 align:middle line:84%
As far as I mean, if you were
to compare latitudes here

00:02:31.990 --> 00:02:34.654 align:middle line:84%
on planet Earth, it was
very, very far north.

00:02:34.654 --> 00:02:36.070 align:middle line:84%
So it was a very,
very cold region

00:02:36.070 --> 00:02:38.620 align:middle line:84%
that we were a part of at a
place called Forward Station

00:02:38.620 --> 00:02:39.460 align:middle line:90%
Zebra.

00:02:39.460 --> 00:02:44.120 align:middle line:84%
And spent the better part of
17 years in the MDF there.

00:02:44.120 --> 00:02:47.009 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Randy, do you
know how wild this sounds?

00:02:47.009 --> 00:02:48.550 align:middle line:84%
>>CRAMER: I've had
some conversations

00:02:48.550 --> 00:02:51.049 align:middle line:84%
with people and yeah, it blows
some people's mind sometimes,

00:02:51.049 --> 00:02:52.060 align:middle line:90%
yeah.

00:02:52.060 --> 00:02:53.860 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Do people believe you?

00:02:53.860 --> 00:02:55.960 align:middle line:84%
>>CRAMER: A lot of
them surprisingly do.

00:02:55.960 --> 00:02:58.480 align:middle line:84%
I mean, to me, when
I say it out loud,

00:02:58.480 --> 00:03:04.100 align:middle line:84%
I understand how outside the
box it sounds, believe me.

00:03:04.100 --> 00:03:06.390 align:middle line:84%
But having
experienced it myself,

00:03:06.390 --> 00:03:09.549 align:middle line:84%
all I'm really talking
about is my own memories,

00:03:09.549 --> 00:03:11.840 align:middle line:84%
my own perspective of how it
happened when I was there.

00:03:11.840 --> 00:03:14.131 align:middle line:84%
So to me, it's a very matter
of fact set of experiences

00:03:14.131 --> 00:03:15.400 align:middle line:90%
because I was there.

00:03:15.400 --> 00:03:18.110 align:middle line:84%
But I get that it's outside the
normal realm of most people's

00:03:18.110 --> 00:03:18.910 align:middle line:90%
experiences.

00:03:18.910 --> 00:03:20.305 align:middle line:90%
And to most people it's a what?

00:03:20.305 --> 00:03:21.430 align:middle line:90%
What are you talking about?

00:03:21.430 --> 00:03:22.230 align:middle line:90%
I get that.

00:03:22.230 --> 00:03:24.670 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: I want to find out
how this project developed--

00:03:24.670 --> 00:03:25.470 align:middle line:90%
>>CRAMER: Sure.

00:03:25.470 --> 00:03:28.300 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: --where it is
today, what other countries

00:03:28.300 --> 00:03:29.525 align:middle line:90%
might be doing like that.

00:03:29.525 --> 00:03:30.400 align:middle line:90%
>>CRAMER: Absolutely.

00:03:30.400 --> 00:03:33.250 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: I'm not here to
doubt you nor am I here

00:03:33.250 --> 00:03:35.114 align:middle line:84%
to destroy your
story by any means.

00:03:35.114 --> 00:03:36.280 align:middle line:90%
>>CRAMER: I appreciate that.

00:03:36.280 --> 00:03:38.890 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: I just want to hear
from you in your own views.

00:03:38.890 --> 00:03:43.310 align:middle line:84%
And then we'll let our "Beyond
Belief" audience decide hey,

00:03:43.310 --> 00:03:46.360 align:middle line:84%
we think this guy's telling
the truth or maybe he isn't.

00:03:46.360 --> 00:03:47.570 align:middle line:90%
But let me ask you this--

00:03:47.570 --> 00:03:48.580 align:middle line:90%
>>CRAMER: Please.

00:03:48.580 --> 00:03:52.150 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: --if you're not telling
the truth that's in quotes, OK?

00:03:52.150 --> 00:03:54.830 align:middle line:84%
Because we're going on
the assumption you are.

00:03:54.830 --> 00:03:55.630 align:middle line:90%
>>CRAMER: Right.

00:03:55.630 --> 00:03:58.900 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: But if you're
not telling the truth,

00:03:58.900 --> 00:04:00.930 align:middle line:84%
what are you
getting out of this?

00:04:00.930 --> 00:04:02.312 align:middle line:90%
>>CRAMER: Not much.

00:04:02.312 --> 00:04:04.770 align:middle line:84%
But I also like to point out,
if I'm not telling the truth,

00:04:04.770 --> 00:04:06.520 align:middle line:84%
then I am committing
a number of felonies,

00:04:06.520 --> 00:04:08.270 align:middle line:84%
including felony
impersonating an officer.

00:04:08.270 --> 00:04:10.394 align:middle line:84%
And I have encouraged people
who think that I'm not

00:04:10.394 --> 00:04:12.270 align:middle line:84%
telling the truth to
report me to the FBI

00:04:12.270 --> 00:04:14.435 align:middle line:84%
or to the CMCs office
in the Marine Corps.

00:04:14.435 --> 00:04:16.560 align:middle line:84%
I know some people who have
had those conversations

00:04:16.560 --> 00:04:18.768 align:middle line:84%
