00:05:27.990 --> 00:05:29.480 align:middle line:90%
>>CRAMER: No, I haven't--

00:05:29.480 --> 00:05:31.620 align:middle line:84%
if anything, in
the last six years,

00:05:31.620 --> 00:05:35.880 align:middle line:84%
it has cost me more than I
have ever possibly potentially

00:05:35.880 --> 00:05:38.880 align:middle line:84%
gained from this in
personal relationships,

00:05:38.880 --> 00:05:43.240 align:middle line:84%
in a destroyed marriage, and
a number of other things.

00:05:43.240 --> 00:05:45.550 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Why, because
they don't believe you?

00:05:45.550 --> 00:05:49.080 align:middle line:84%
>>CRAMER: I don't even want
to discuss the particulars

00:05:49.080 --> 00:05:50.010 align:middle line:90%
of that situation.

00:05:50.010 --> 00:05:52.860 align:middle line:90%
Let's just say that it was--

00:05:52.860 --> 00:05:54.780 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Well, let me
rephrase the question.

00:05:54.780 --> 00:05:57.985 align:middle line:84%
Did what you're telling us
today affect your marriage?

00:05:57.985 --> 00:05:59.610 align:middle line:84%
>>CRAMER: Let's just
say that another--

00:05:59.610 --> 00:06:06.150 align:middle line:84%
a third party took advantage of
a situation in which they felt

00:06:06.150 --> 00:06:09.355 align:middle line:84%
could be exploited with
someone else's insecurities.

00:06:09.355 --> 00:06:11.730 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: All right, so they
took advantage of a weakness.

00:06:11.730 --> 00:06:12.050 align:middle line:90%
>>CRAMER: Yeah.

00:06:12.050 --> 00:06:13.500 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: I'm
reading the picture.

00:06:13.500 --> 00:06:16.740 align:middle line:84%
>>CRAMER: But to say that
when my ex-wife and I met,

00:06:16.740 --> 00:06:20.457 align:middle line:84%
she was a firm believer
in my telling the truth.

00:06:20.457 --> 00:06:21.540 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: And that changed?

00:06:21.540 --> 00:06:22.664 align:middle line:90%
>>CRAMER: And that changed.

00:06:22.664 --> 00:06:24.360 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Does that
disappoint you?

00:06:24.360 --> 00:06:25.610 align:middle line:90%
>>CRAMER: It's heartbreaking.

00:06:25.610 --> 00:06:26.410 align:middle line:90%
But again--

00:06:26.410 --> 00:06:26.740 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: I'm sorry.

00:06:26.740 --> 00:06:28.110 align:middle line:84%
>>CRAMER: --I'm not really
here to talk about that.

00:06:28.110 --> 00:06:30.110 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: And I'm sorry
to had to go through that

00:06:30.110 --> 00:06:32.490 align:middle line:84%
and thank you for sharing
part of that with us.

00:06:32.490 --> 00:06:33.750 align:middle line:90%
I appreciate that.

00:06:33.750 --> 00:06:36.420 align:middle line:84%
You're not the first
person to come forward

00:06:36.420 --> 00:06:38.094 align:middle line:84%
with these kinds of
incredible stories.

00:06:38.094 --> 00:06:39.510 align:middle line:84%
>>CRAMER: And I
won't be the last.

00:06:39.510 --> 00:06:41.970 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: And that leads us
to believe that something's

00:06:41.970 --> 00:06:44.540 align:middle line:90%
going on, whatever it may be.

00:06:44.540 --> 00:06:45.340 align:middle line:90%
>>CRAMER: For sure.

00:06:45.340 --> 00:06:48.390 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: So let's go back
to the recruitment portion.

00:06:48.390 --> 00:06:52.480 align:middle line:84%
I want to look at a little
video from "Deep Space: Inside

00:06:52.480 --> 00:06:53.280 align:middle line:90%
the Program."

00:06:53.280 --> 00:06:54.080 align:middle line:90%
Here we go.

00:06:54.080 --> 00:06:55.480 align:middle line:90%
>>CRAMER: Oh, yeah.

00:06:55.480 --> 00:06:57.760 align:middle line:10%
>>NARRATOR: If there is
a breakaway civilization

00:06:57.760 --> 00:07:00.340 align:middle line:10%
how do they get
people to join them?

00:07:00.340 --> 00:07:04.000 align:middle line:10%
Is there a recruitment process?

00:07:04.000 --> 00:07:05.650 align:middle line:10%
We shall discover
that getting people

00:07:05.650 --> 00:07:07.900 align:middle line:10%
to join the Secret
Space Program is more

00:07:07.900 --> 00:07:09.640 align:middle line:10%
complex than first imagined.

00:07:09.640 --> 00:07:14.070 align:middle line:90%


00:07:14.070 --> 00:07:16.200 align:middle line:90%
Some are asked.

00:07:16.200 --> 00:07:18.670 align:middle line:10%
Some are made.

00:07:18.670 --> 00:07:22.554 align:middle line:10%
And some appear to be
taken against their will.

00:07:22.554 --> 00:07:24.220 align:middle line:10%
>>LAURA EISENHOWER:
There's recruitments

00:07:24.220 --> 00:07:25.719 align:middle line:10%
where certain
individuals are picked

00:07:25.719 --> 00:07:30.250 align:middle line:10%
to participate in
projects and to be

00:07:30.250 --> 00:07:32.020 align:middle line:10%
a part of particular agendas.

00:07:32.020 --> 00:07:33.880 align:middle line:10%
I have an experience
myself of being

00:07:33.880 --> 00:07:37.432 align:middle line:10%
recruited to go off planet in
2006 to join a Mars colony.

00:07:37.432 --> 00:07:38.890 align:middle line:10%
And so there's
specific reasons why

00:07:38.890 --> 00:07:40.181 align:middle line:10%
certain individuals are picked.

00:07:40.181 --> 00:07:44.170 align:middle line:10%
And to get to the bottom of
it is not the easiest thing

00:07:44.170 --> 00:07:46.570 align:middle line:10%
because I mean, you're
unraveling a huge mystery.

00:07:46.570 --> 00:07:49.570 align:middle line:10%
I mean, there's things like
quantum access technologies

00:07:49.570 --> 00:07:51.940 align:middle line:10%
that are used to
target individuals.

00:07:51.940 --> 00:07:54.100 align:middle line:10%
What I discovered in
my recruitment process

00:07:54.100 --> 00:07:57.377 align:middle line:10%
is something called Looking
Glass Technologies was used

00:07:57.377 --> 00:07:58.960 align:middle line:10%
and something called
the Orion's Cube.

00:07:58.960 --> 00:08:02.170 align:middle line:10%
These were names that were
in the emails connected

00:08:02.170 --> 00:08:04.510 align:middle line:10%
to how I was chosen.

00:08:04.510 --> 00:08:08.470 align:middle line:10%
And this isn't just tracking me
in this particular incarnation,

00:08:08.470 --> 00:08:10.990 align:middle line:10%
there is a pre-targeting
before I was born.

00:08:10.990 --> 00:08:12.715 align:middle line:10%
So a lot of strategies
are in place.

00:08:12.715 --> 00:08:15.310 align:middle line:10%
Or if we kind of look at
the bigger picture in some

00:08:15.310 --> 00:08:17.740 align:middle line:10%
of these controller groups
and how they manage timelines

00:08:17.740 --> 00:08:19.510 align:middle line:10%
and how they work with
these technologies

00:08:19.510 --> 00:08:22.724 align:middle line:10%
to achieve a specific
desired result.

00:08:22.724 --> 00:08:24.890 align:middle line:10%
These things have been in
the works for a long time.

00:08:24.890 --> 00:08:30.610 align:middle line:10%
And so when we look at different
elements of like the defense

00:08:30.610 --> 00:08:33.220 align:middle line:10%
departments and things that
happened after the Second World

00:08:33.220 --> 00:08:38.350 align:middle line:10%
War, we're dealing with
certain agendas that had

00:08:38.350 --> 00:08:41.159 align:middle line:10%
good intentions to start with.

00:08:41.159 --> 00:08:42.152 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Wow.

00:08:42.152 --> 00:08:43.110 align:middle line:90%
>>CRAMER: I love Laura.

00:08:43.110 --> 00:08:44.020 align:middle line:90%
She's fabulous.

00:08:44.020 --> 00:08:44.910 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: She's a great person.

00:08:44.910 --> 00:08:45.460 align:middle line:90%
>>CRAMER: Oh, yeah.

00:08:45.460 --> 00:08:46.540 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: A dedicated researcher.

00:08:46.540 --> 00:08:48.498 align:middle line:84%
>>CRAMER: I know her very
well, she's fabulous.

00:08:48.498 --> 00:08:50.970 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: So Captain, let's go
back to the beginning then.

00:08:50.970 --> 00:08:54.630 align:middle line:84%
Was your family involved in this
at all or were you the first?

00:08:54.630 --> 00:08:57.750 align:middle line:90%


00:08:57.750 --> 00:09:00.810 align:middle line:84%
>>CRAMER: I'm pretty certain
that my older siblings were

00:09:00.810 --> 00:09:04.740 align:middle line:84%
also put into programs
because of the family's

00:09:04.740 --> 00:09:05.670 align:middle line:90%
genetic heritage.

00:09:05.670 --> 00:09:07.800 align:middle line:84%
And then whatever
mingling that they

00:09:07.800 --> 00:09:13.110 align:middle line:84%
decided to do at the pre-birth
and birthing process.

00:09:13.110 --> 00:09:15.600 align:middle line:84%
Both of my siblings
exhibited early childhood

00:09:15.600 --> 00:09:20.750 align:middle line:84%
post-traumatic stress
disorder symptoms, like I did.

00:09:20.750 --> 00:09:23.800 align:middle line:84%
But I seemed to have a better
set of coping mechanisms

00:09:23.800 --> 00:09:24.600 align:middle line:90%
than they did.

00:09:24.600 --> 00:09:27.780 align:middle line:84%
So I'm not in complete
denial about my existence

00:09:27.780 --> 00:09:28.650 align:middle line:90%
at this point.

00:09:28.650 --> 00:09:30.233 align:middle line:84%
So I wouldn't say
that I was the first

00:09:30.233 --> 00:09:32.520 align:middle line:84%
but I would say that
I was probably a more

00:09:32.520 --> 00:09:34.200 align:middle line:90%
perfected version by the--

00:09:34.200 --> 00:09:37.650 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Did you go willingly
or did they pull you in to it?

00:09:37.650 --> 00:09:39.360 align:middle line:90%
>>CRAMER: Oh, I was--

00:09:39.360 --> 00:09:42.750 align:middle line:84%
from what I understand is
that it's been told to me

00:09:42.750 --> 00:09:44.490 align:middle line:84%
there was a drawing
board process

00:09:44.490 --> 00:09:47.940 align:middle line:84%
in which part of my mother's
DNA and my father's DNA

00:09:47.940 --> 00:09:49.060 align:middle line:90%
were laid out.

00:09:49.060 --> 00:09:52.410 align:middle line:84%
And then they decided which
parts they wanted to change.

00:09:52.410 --> 00:09:56.580 align:middle line:84%
So my entire genetic code
was written in a laboratory

00:09:56.580 --> 00:10:00.000 align:middle line:84%
before I was actually even
created as a life form.

00:10:00.000 --> 00:10:03.060 align:middle line:84%
So I was built from the
ground up as a person.

00:10:03.060 --> 00:10:05.260 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Have you undergone
hypnotic regression?

00:10:05.260 --> 00:10:06.060 align:middle line:90%
>>CRAMER: Sure.

00:10:06.060 --> 00:10:08.430 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: And what
do they tell you?

00:10:08.430 --> 00:10:10.800 align:middle line:84%
>>CRAMER: Just recovered
more clarified memories

00:10:10.800 --> 00:10:12.800 align:middle line:84%
of my experiences
really more than usual.

00:10:12.800 --> 00:10:14.430 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: But those experiences
come out in the end.

00:10:14.430 --> 00:10:15.680 align:middle line:90%
>>CRAMER: Oh yeah, absolutely.

00:10:15.680 --> 00:10:19.470 align:middle line:84%
But I would point out
that hypnosis is just

00:10:19.470 --> 00:10:24.060 align:middle line:84%
trying to get your brain into
a natural alpha or theta state,

00:10:24.060 --> 00:10:26.340 align:middle line:90%
which meditation does anyway.

00:10:26.340 --> 00:10:28.710 align:middle line:84%
And so most of my
memory retrieval

00:10:28.710 --> 00:10:31.950 align:middle line:84%
is through meditation process
to get into theta states.

00:10:31.950 --> 00:10:34.009 align:middle line:84%
But hypnosis is just
someone else walking you

00:10:34.009 --> 00:10:36.050 align:middle line:84%
through that process to
get to those theta states

00:10:36.050 --> 00:10:37.580 align:middle line:84%
so that you can
retrieve your memory.

00:10:37.580 --> 00:10:39.390 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Well, your brain
is like a tape recorder.

00:10:39.390 --> 00:10:39.620 align:middle line:90%
>>CRAMER: Absolutely.

00:10:39.620 --> 00:10:41.036 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: And I
think what hypnosis

00:10:41.036 --> 00:10:45.540 align:middle line:84%
does is it rewinds that
tape in a strategic way

00:10:45.540 --> 00:10:46.650 align:middle line:90%
to get the answers.

00:10:46.650 --> 00:10:48.120 align:middle line:84%
I've always been
convinced, Randy,

00:10:48.120 --> 00:10:49.950 align:middle line:84%
that if you looked
at a crowd of 1,000

00:10:49.950 --> 00:10:52.140 align:middle line:84%
people and people
would just say, hey,

00:10:52.140 --> 00:10:54.120 align:middle line:90%
was George Noory in that crowd?

00:10:54.120 --> 00:10:55.900 align:middle line:90%
You'd probably say I don't know.

00:10:55.900 --> 00:10:56.700 align:middle line:90%
I couldn't see him.

00:10:56.700 --> 00:11:01.050 align:middle line:84%
But under hypnosis,
it's in your brain

00:11:01.050 --> 00:11:03.900 align:middle line:84%
and I think you could
pinpoint yeah, he was.

00:11:03.900 --> 00:11:06.000 align:middle line:84%
He was in the fourth
row on the left.

00:11:06.000 --> 00:11:07.030 align:middle line:90%
It happens like that.

00:11:07.030 --> 00:11:09.390 align:middle line:84%
Now, in this particular
case with you,

00:11:09.390 --> 00:11:12.390 align:middle line:84%
this secret program
that was done,

00:11:12.390 --> 00:11:15.599 align:middle line:84%
how many people do you think
are involved in it today?

00:11:15.599 --> 00:11:16.890 align:middle line:90%
>>CRAMER: Oh goodness gracious.

00:11:16.890 --> 00:11:20.220 align:middle line:84%
I mean, if you want to talk
about the covert military space

00:11:20.220 --> 00:11:21.990 align:middle line:84%
program or Secret
Space Program at large,

00:11:21.990 --> 00:11:24.900 align:middle line:84%
you're talking about hundreds of
thousands potentially millions

00:11:24.900 --> 00:11:26.490 align:middle line:90%
of people but at this point.

00:11:26.490 --> 00:11:28.620 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Are they all
knowledgeable of what's

00:11:28.620 --> 00:11:33.259 align:middle line:84%
happening to them or are they
walking around in a daze?

00:11:33.259 --> 00:11:34.800 align:middle line:84%
>>CRAMER: It's all
compartmentalized.

00:11:34.800 --> 00:11:38.640 align:middle line:84%
So depending on where you are,
what stage of your service in,

00:11:38.640 --> 00:11:43.530 align:middle line:84%
or whether they've sent you back
and put the quote unquote "back

00:11:43.530 --> 00:11:47.850 align:middle line:84%
into your timeline to live
out your fate or your destiny"

00:11:47.850 --> 00:11:50.030 align:middle line:90%
as sometimes it's referred to.

00:11:50.030 --> 00:11:51.780 align:middle line:84%
And most of the time,
most of those people

00:11:51.780 --> 00:11:53.640 align:middle line:84%
are returned with
repressed memories.

00:11:53.640 --> 00:11:55.590 align:middle line:84%
So they don't
remember much of it.

00:11:55.590 --> 00:11:58.410 align:middle line:84%
They often have,
like I did, a series

00:11:58.410 --> 00:12:01.410 align:middle line:84%
of emotional, psychological
attachments or traumas

00:12:01.410 --> 00:12:02.820 align:middle line:84%
associated with
their experience.

00:12:02.820 --> 00:12:05.290 align:middle line:84%
But the linear conscious
memory is often detached.

00:12:05.290 --> 00:12:07.320 align:middle line:84%
But if you're still in
service, then you're

00:12:07.320 --> 00:12:09.540 align:middle line:84%
actively remembering what's
going on at that time.

00:12:09.540 --> 00:12:11.910 align:middle line:84%
But for security
reasons they pretty much

00:12:11.910 --> 00:12:14.320 align:middle line:84%
suppress people's memories
when they return them,

00:12:14.320 --> 00:12:16.890 align:middle line:84%
so I'd say that the
majority of people

00:12:16.890 --> 00:12:20.100 align:middle line:84%
who have returned
from service have

00:12:20.100 --> 00:12:22.417 align:middle line:84%
little or no understanding
or memory of what

00:12:22.417 --> 00:12:23.250 align:middle line:90%
they've experienced.

00:12:23.250 --> 00:12:25.260 align:middle line:84%
I get e-mails from
people all the time

00:12:25.260 --> 00:12:27.730 align:middle line:84%
who are in the process of
recovering memory, that

00:12:27.730 --> 00:12:29.270 align:middle line:84%
are in the process
of getting there.

00:12:29.270 --> 00:12:31.530 align:middle line:84%
But were absolutely
not even at a stage

00:12:31.530 --> 00:12:34.119 align:middle line:84%
where they want to go
public or do an interview.

00:12:34.119 --> 00:12:36.160 align:middle line:84%
I mean, it's the last
thing that they want to do.

00:12:36.160 --> 00:12:37.290 align:middle line:84%
They're still trying
to figure out what's

00:12:37.290 --> 00:12:38.331 align:middle line:90%
going on with themselves.

00:12:38.331 --> 00:12:40.170 align:middle line:90%
They're in an earlier state.

00:12:40.170 --> 00:12:42.520 align:middle line:84%
When I say "earlier state"
that I was in myself,

00:12:42.520 --> 00:12:45.410 align:middle line:84%
which is very
confusing because--

00:12:45.410 --> 00:12:46.650 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Is it frustrating?

00:12:46.650 --> 00:12:49.350 align:middle line:84%
>>CRAMER: Incredibly because
you get these memories-- they're

00:12:49.350 --> 00:12:50.730 align:middle line:90%
very clear, they're very vivid.

00:12:50.730 --> 00:12:52.260 align:middle line:84%
They're often
incredibly visceral

00:12:52.260 --> 00:12:54.440 align:middle line:90%
and emotionally traumatic.

00:12:54.440 --> 00:12:57.000 align:middle line:84%
But because they don't
match a linear map

00:12:57.000 --> 00:12:59.700 align:middle line:84%
to what you think you
understand your life is,

00:12:59.700 --> 00:13:01.330 align:middle line:90%
it doesn't make any sense.

00:13:01.330 --> 00:13:04.260 align:middle line:84%
And so while you're missing
those linear components,

00:13:04.260 --> 00:13:06.780 align:middle line:84%
you're like well,
OK, I remember this.

00:13:06.780 --> 00:13:08.190 align:middle line:90%
It feels incredibly real.

00:13:08.190 --> 00:13:09.120 align:middle line:90%
It feels traumatic.

00:13:09.120 --> 00:13:10.470 align:middle line:90%
It's very vivid.

00:13:10.470 --> 00:13:12.330 align:middle line:84%
But where's the
linear connection?

00:13:12.330 --> 00:13:14.167 align:middle line:84%
How in the world
did I get there?

00:13:14.167 --> 00:13:15.750 align:middle line:84%
And so a lot of
people don't know what

00:13:15.750 --> 00:13:16.958 align:middle line:90%
to make of their experiences.

00:13:16.958 --> 00:13:19.567 align:middle line:84%
Or they do like I did for
a certain amount of time,

00:13:19.567 --> 00:13:21.150 align:middle line:84%
which is question
their mental health.

00:13:21.150 --> 00:13:23.910 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: I was going to say, did
you think you were going crazy?

00:13:23.910 --> 00:13:26.280 align:middle line:90%
>>CRAMER: At times, absolutely.

00:13:26.280 --> 00:13:29.310 align:middle line:84%
The thing that changed that,
which I was so grateful for,

00:13:29.310 --> 00:13:31.699 align:middle line:84%
I had a very dear friend who
is a psychiatrist, actually.

00:13:31.699 --> 00:13:33.240 align:middle line:84%
And we were sitting
in my living room

00:13:33.240 --> 00:13:35.280 align:middle line:90%
one day having a cup of tea.

00:13:35.280 --> 00:13:38.726 align:middle line:84%
And I said to him, you know, I'm
really not sure what's going on

00:13:38.726 --> 00:13:39.850 align:middle line:90%
with my head at the moment.

00:13:39.850 --> 00:13:43.660 align:middle line:84%
I said, I either have
this amazing, crazy case

00:13:43.660 --> 00:13:45.100 align:middle line:84%
of post-traumatic
stress disorder

00:13:45.100 --> 00:13:47.564 align:middle line:84%
that I need to sort out
or I'm absolutely bonkers.

00:13:47.564 --> 00:13:49.480 align:middle line:84%
And I'm really not sure
where to go with that.

00:13:49.480 --> 00:13:51.610 align:middle line:84%
And he was so cool
and calm about it.

00:13:51.610 --> 00:13:54.100 align:middle line:84%
And he was like, well, OK,
let's break out the book.

00:13:54.100 --> 00:13:55.802 align:middle line:84%
And he pulled out
the DSM-IV, which

00:13:55.802 --> 00:13:57.010 align:middle line:90%
it was the four at that time.

00:13:57.010 --> 00:13:57.550 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Right.

00:13:57.550 --> 00:13:59.750 align:middle line:84%
>>CRAMER: And said, let's
look at your symptoms.

00:13:59.750 --> 00:14:02.004 align:middle line:84%
Let's look at all of
these other possibilities.

00:14:02.004 --> 00:14:03.170 align:middle line:90%
Let's look at schizophrenia.

00:14:03.170 --> 00:14:04.794 align:middle line:84%
Let's look at
schizoaffective disorder.

00:14:04.794 --> 00:14:06.290 align:middle line:90%
Let's look at bipolar disorder.

00:14:06.290 --> 00:14:07.580 align:middle line:84%
And we went through
them one at a time.

00:14:07.580 --> 00:14:08.080 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Ruled them all out.

00:14:08.080 --> 00:14:08.920 align:middle line:84%
>>CRAMER: And we
ruled them all out

00:14:08.920 --> 00:14:10.878 align:middle line:84%
until we got to post-traumatic
stress disorder.

00:14:10.878 --> 00:14:13.610 align:middle line:84%
And it was you know, 1, 2, 3,
4, all the way down the line.

00:14:13.610 --> 00:14:17.620 align:middle line:84%
So it was, at that point,
I felt medically convinced

00:14:17.620 --> 00:14:19.540 align:middle line:84%
by a medical
professional that we had

00:14:19.540 --> 00:14:21.400 align:middle line:90%
looked at my behavioral health.

00:14:21.400 --> 00:14:22.930 align:middle line:84%
I did not have
enough of symptoms

00:14:22.930 --> 00:14:25.360 align:middle line:84%
to be labeled or
classified as any

00:14:25.360 --> 00:14:27.290 align:middle line:84%
of the other behavioral
health conditions.

00:14:27.290 --> 00:14:31.092 align:middle line:84%
And I had a solid link to
medical post-traumatic stress

00:14:31.092 --> 00:14:33.550 align:middle line:84%
disorder, which then meant that
the experiences that I were

00:14:33.550 --> 00:14:35.680 align:middle line:84%
having were in
fact real traumatic

00:14:35.680 --> 00:14:37.930 align:middle line:84%
experiences that
I had to sort out.

00:14:37.930 --> 00:14:39.760 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Are you
in the program now?

00:14:39.760 --> 00:14:41.080 align:middle line:90%
>>CRAMER: Which program?

00:14:41.080 --> 00:14:44.507 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: The Mars
or the Moon program?

00:14:44.507 --> 00:14:46.840 align:middle line:84%
>>CRAMER: I'm still a part
of United States Marine Corps

00:14:46.840 --> 00:14:48.220 align:middle line:90%
Special Section.

00:14:48.220 --> 00:14:49.960 align:middle line:84%
Officers have life
commissions, which

00:14:49.960 --> 00:14:53.300 align:middle line:84%
means I don't ever get to
get out until the day I die.

00:14:53.300 --> 00:14:54.570 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Like the CIA.

00:14:54.570 --> 00:14:55.775 align:middle line:90%
Once you're in, you're in.

00:14:55.775 --> 00:14:56.575 align:middle line:90%
Like the mob.

00:14:56.575 --> 00:14:58.640 align:middle line:84%
>>CRAMER: A little bit--
yeah, a little bit.

00:14:58.640 --> 00:15:01.270 align:middle line:84%
And so I will
continue to do my work

00:15:01.270 --> 00:15:04.300 align:middle line:84%
and be associated with them
and have communications

00:15:04.300 --> 00:15:06.160 align:middle line:90%
with the command staff.

00:15:06.160 --> 00:15:08.440 align:middle line:84%
But I'm definitely
in a unique position

00:15:08.440 --> 00:15:12.100 align:middle line:84%
where there's plenty of other
people within the program that

00:15:12.100 --> 00:15:14.480 align:middle line:90%
don't want me talking publicly.

00:15:14.480 --> 00:15:16.090 align:middle line:90%
And plenty of other people--

00:15:16.090 --> 00:15:17.950 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Why are you
talking publicly?

00:15:17.950 --> 00:15:19.450 align:middle line:84%
>>CRAMER: Because my Brigadier
General and the command

00:15:19.450 --> 00:15:21.240 align:middle line:90%
staff asked me to talk publicly.

00:15:21.240 --> 00:15:21.580 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Really.

00:15:21.580 --> 00:15:21.990 align:middle line:90%
Why?

00:15:21.990 --> 00:15:22.790 align:middle line:90%
>>CRAMER: Yeah.

00:15:22.790 --> 00:15:25.660 align:middle line:84%
Well, they feel-- well, I
guess the long and short

00:15:25.660 --> 00:15:29.380 align:middle line:84%
of that is they feel
that the conversations

00:15:29.380 --> 00:15:32.380 align:middle line:84%
with our extraterrestrial
friends and business partners

00:15:32.380 --> 00:15:35.984 align:middle line:84%
has been that we're supposed to
have a global disclosure moment

00:15:35.984 --> 00:15:38.650 align:middle line:84%
so that people can come into the
know and the awareness of that.

00:15:38.650 --> 00:15:41.100 align:middle line:84%
So that we can be
making when I say "we,"

00:15:41.100 --> 00:15:44.920 align:middle line:84%
we as an entire
civilization as the people

00:15:44.920 --> 00:15:47.135 align:middle line:84%
can make informed decisions
about what's going on

00:15:47.135 --> 00:15:48.010 align:middle line:90%
and what we're doing.

00:15:48.010 --> 00:15:51.400 align:middle line:84%
People can't vote and then
make an informed decision.

00:15:51.400 --> 00:15:53.749 align:middle line:84%
There's no real democracy
making informed decisions

00:15:53.749 --> 00:15:56.290 align:middle line:84%
so people don't know the truth
about what they're voting for,

00:15:56.290 --> 00:15:57.884 align:middle line:90%
what decisions they're making.

00:15:57.884 --> 00:15:59.800 align:middle line:84%
So there are a number
of extraterrestrials who

00:15:59.800 --> 00:16:02.072 align:middle line:90%
believe that that's important.

00:16:02.072 --> 00:16:04.030 align:middle line:84%
That it's important that
people aren't lied to.

00:16:04.030 --> 00:16:05.740 align:middle line:84%
That it's important we
don't lie to the public.

00:16:05.740 --> 00:16:07.531 align:middle line:84%
That it's important
that we bring everybody

00:16:07.531 --> 00:16:09.070 align:middle line:90%
into a truthful awareness.

00:16:09.070 --> 00:16:11.740 align:middle line:84%
So there's has been this
conversation for decades

00:16:11.740 --> 00:16:13.990 align:middle line:90%
on when that's supposed to be.

00:16:13.990 --> 00:16:16.615 align:middle line:84%
The command staff
feels like that we

00:16:16.615 --> 00:16:18.610 align:middle line:84%
and when I use this
other "we," that those

00:16:18.610 --> 00:16:21.640 align:middle line:84%
within the covert military
space program projects

00:16:21.640 --> 00:16:24.130 align:middle line:84%
have delayed and delayed
and delayed and delayed

00:16:24.130 --> 00:16:27.690 align:middle line:84%
that process to the point
of it harming civilization

00:16:27.690 --> 00:16:28.490 align:middle line:90%
as we know it.

00:16:28.490 --> 00:16:33.640 align:middle line:84%
And so the command staff decided
with a lot of other personnel,

00:16:33.640 --> 00:16:36.790 align:middle line:84%
with a lot of other officers
within Radiant Guardian,

00:16:36.790 --> 00:16:39.130 align:middle line:84%
that they needed to
pick a spokesperson

00:16:39.130 --> 00:16:42.160 align:middle line:84%
to have a conversation to
talk to the general public.

00:16:42.160 --> 00:16:44.622 align:middle line:84%
And there was a short
list of officers,

00:16:44.622 --> 00:16:46.330 align:middle line:84%
from what I understand,
at first and that

00:16:46.330 --> 00:16:48.730 align:middle line:84%
