00:56:31.870 --> 00:56:34.660 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Yet your soul and your
personality and everything--

00:56:34.660 --> 00:56:36.610 align:middle line:90%
memory has all been transferred?

00:56:36.610 --> 00:56:38.290 align:middle line:90%
>>CRAMER: Absolutely

00:56:38.290 --> 00:56:41.170 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: I'm not sure about
the soul being able to do that.

00:56:41.170 --> 00:56:42.070 align:middle line:90%
Memory maybe.

00:56:42.070 --> 00:56:44.466 align:middle line:84%
They may have that ability
to download and transfer.

00:56:44.466 --> 00:56:46.090 align:middle line:84%
>>CRAMER: Well, again,
my understanding

00:56:46.090 --> 00:56:49.060 align:middle line:84%
is that the soul is a
quantum fluid dynamic

00:56:49.060 --> 00:56:51.080 align:middle line:84%
and so being a
quantum fluid dynamic

00:56:51.080 --> 00:56:54.610 align:middle line:84%
it can be quote unquote
"pumped from one vessel

00:56:54.610 --> 00:56:55.990 align:middle line:90%
and put back into another."

00:56:55.990 --> 00:56:58.780 align:middle line:84%
Again, that's not my area
so I couldn't tell you how

00:56:58.780 --> 00:57:00.060 align:middle line:90%
the science works behind that.

00:57:00.060 --> 00:57:02.885 align:middle line:84%
But from the way I've
had it explained to me,

00:57:02.885 --> 00:57:03.760 align:middle line:90%
that's how it's done.

00:57:03.760 --> 00:57:05.140 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: What happened
to your old body?

00:57:05.140 --> 00:57:05.980 align:middle line:90%
Where is it now?

00:57:05.980 --> 00:57:07.870 align:middle line:84%
>>CRAMER: In the
incinerator I'm sure.

00:57:07.870 --> 00:57:09.619 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Does it bother you?

00:57:09.619 --> 00:57:10.660 align:middle line:90%
>>CRAMER: No, not really.

00:57:10.660 --> 00:57:12.250 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Does it feel like you?

00:57:12.250 --> 00:57:13.150 align:middle line:90%
>>CRAMER: It does.

00:57:13.150 --> 00:57:15.220 align:middle line:84%
I mean, as much as it
should be because I look--

00:57:15.220 --> 00:57:16.130 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Can I touch your hands?

00:57:16.130 --> 00:57:16.450 align:middle line:90%
>>CRAMER: Yeah, sure.

00:57:16.450 --> 00:57:17.770 align:middle line:84%
I mean, I look in the
mirror and I see--

00:57:17.770 --> 00:57:18.430 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: You're human.

00:57:18.430 --> 00:57:19.846 align:middle line:84%
>>CRAMER: --I see
me looking back.

00:57:19.846 --> 00:57:24.530 align:middle line:84%
So it feels like me as
much as it could be.

00:57:24.530 --> 00:57:27.077 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Was this body
made in a laboratory?

00:57:27.077 --> 00:57:28.660 align:middle line:84%
>>CRAMER: As near
as I can understand.

00:57:28.660 --> 00:57:30.529 align:middle line:90%
Yeah, hatched out of a clone.

00:57:30.529 --> 00:57:32.570 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Same with your
face and everything else?

00:57:32.570 --> 00:57:34.230 align:middle line:84%
You were a total
clone of who you were?

00:57:34.230 --> 00:57:36.830 align:middle line:84%
>>CRAMER: The physical
body absolutely, yeah.

00:57:36.830 --> 00:57:39.064 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Yet you have
memory from your past.

00:57:39.064 --> 00:57:41.230 align:middle line:84%
>>CRAMER: Right, because
they take everything that's

00:57:41.230 --> 00:57:44.110 align:middle line:84%
internal into the old body
and put it into the new one

00:57:44.110 --> 00:57:46.625 align:middle line:90%
and you're just the same person.

00:57:46.625 --> 00:57:48.250 align:middle line:84%
You look in the
mirror, you're younger.

00:57:48.250 --> 00:57:49.750 align:middle line:90%
But it's the same you.

00:57:49.750 --> 00:57:52.164 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Feels like "The
Island of Doctor Moreau."

00:57:52.164 --> 00:57:53.830 align:middle line:84%
>>CRAMER: It's a
little weird sometimes.

00:57:53.830 --> 00:57:57.280 align:middle line:84%
If I think about it too
much, it will like twist

00:57:57.280 --> 00:57:58.294 align:middle line:90%
my brain a little bit.

00:57:58.294 --> 00:57:59.960 align:middle line:84%
So I try not to think
about it too much.

00:57:59.960 --> 00:58:02.350 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Is it
difficult for you now

00:58:02.350 --> 00:58:05.620 align:middle line:84%
to have a relationship
because of all of this?

00:58:05.620 --> 00:58:08.530 align:middle line:90%
>>CRAMER: It can be a strain.

00:58:08.530 --> 00:58:09.520 align:middle line:90%
It can be a strain.

00:58:09.520 --> 00:58:12.160 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Do you cry?

00:58:12.160 --> 00:58:15.040 align:middle line:84%
>>CRAMER: I can have all kinds
of emotions about the process

00:58:15.040 --> 00:58:15.970 align:middle line:90%
at different times.

00:58:15.970 --> 00:58:20.740 align:middle line:84%
But I'm also completely
OK with who I am.

00:58:20.740 --> 00:58:22.420 align:middle line:90%
I'm completely OK with who I am.

00:58:22.420 --> 00:58:24.420 align:middle line:84%
I'm OK being in the
skin that I'm in.

00:58:24.420 --> 00:58:27.220 align:middle line:84%
I'm OK having my
experiences that I've had.

00:58:27.220 --> 00:58:29.524 align:middle line:84%
I'm OK knowing that I have
to live my life the way

00:58:29.524 --> 00:58:30.690 align:middle line:90%
that I have to live my life.

00:58:30.690 --> 00:58:31.720 align:middle line:90%
So I'm OK with me.

00:58:31.720 --> 00:58:33.178 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: And you
would do it again?

00:58:33.178 --> 00:58:35.410 align:middle line:84%
>>CRAMER: And anybody who's
not OK with me, that's

00:58:35.410 --> 00:58:36.850 align:middle line:90%
their problem but not mine.

00:58:36.850 --> 00:58:39.100 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: But you'd do it
again, this same program?

00:58:39.100 --> 00:58:41.960 align:middle line:84%
>>CRAMER: Again, not necessarily
by choice but at the same time

00:58:41.960 --> 00:58:43.960 align:middle line:84%
I wouldn't undo the
experiences that I've had.

00:58:43.960 --> 00:58:45.751 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Are you glad
it's happened to you?

00:58:45.751 --> 00:58:48.250 align:middle line:90%


00:58:48.250 --> 00:58:51.676 align:middle line:84%
Or would you prefer
that it never did?

00:58:51.676 --> 00:58:53.300 align:middle line:84%
>>CRAMER: I kind of
have to think of it

00:58:53.300 --> 00:58:58.930 align:middle line:84%
like my tour of duty is like
a giant crap milkshake filled

00:58:58.930 --> 00:59:01.420 align:middle line:84%
with crap up to here with
whipped cream and a cherry

00:59:01.420 --> 00:59:02.320 align:middle line:90%
on top.

00:59:02.320 --> 00:59:04.030 align:middle line:90%
And so I had to go through--

00:59:04.030 --> 00:59:06.280 align:middle line:84%
finish off a whole
crap milkshake.

00:59:06.280 --> 00:59:09.220 align:middle line:84%
But then at the end, there was
this whipped cream and cherry

00:59:09.220 --> 00:59:11.596 align:middle line:84%
on the top that kind
of almost makes it

00:59:11.596 --> 00:59:13.970 align:middle line:84%
worth it that I just wouldn't
want to trade anything for.

00:59:13.970 --> 00:59:16.087 align:middle line:90%
So I just accept both with that.

00:59:16.087 --> 00:59:17.670 align:middle line:84%
Accept the good and
the bad with that.

00:59:17.670 --> 00:59:20.666 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: What's the title
of your upcoming book?

00:59:20.666 --> 00:59:22.790 align:middle line:84%
>>CRAMER: We haven't secured
the ISBN number for it

00:59:22.790 --> 00:59:25.790 align:middle line:84%
yet so I'm keeping it under my
hat until we're actually done.

00:59:25.790 --> 00:59:27.220 align:middle line:90%
But it will be--

00:59:27.220 --> 00:59:32.050 align:middle line:84%
I don't know when we're going to
air this but from today's date,

00:59:32.050 --> 00:59:34.380 align:middle line:84%
it should be any time within
the next couple of months.

00:59:34.380 --> 00:59:36.505 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: And it's on this
subject matter obviously.

00:59:36.505 --> 00:59:39.220 align:middle line:84%
>>CRAMER: Oh it's the
volume one of three

00:59:39.220 --> 00:59:41.590 align:middle line:84%
that is going to be my
memoirs, which will basically

00:59:41.590 --> 00:59:42.595 align:middle line:90%
be my Mars experience.

00:59:42.595 --> 00:59:44.470 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: So you're going
public in a big way?

00:59:44.470 --> 00:59:45.490 align:middle line:90%
>>CRAMER: Absolutely, yeah.

00:59:45.490 --> 00:59:46.573 align:middle line:10%
And I've been working on--

00:59:46.573 --> 00:59:48.970 align:middle line:10%
I've been told that I should
work on it for the last six

00:59:48.970 --> 00:59:51.370 align:middle line:10%
years and it's just been
such a traumatic process

00:59:51.370 --> 00:59:54.160 align:middle line:10%
to sit down and try and
write the experiences

00:59:54.160 --> 00:59:57.790 align:middle line:10%
that it's just been a back and
forth, back and forth process.

00:59:57.790 --> 01:00:00.190 align:middle line:84%
And I just kind of
had to end up in

01:00:00.190 --> 01:00:04.370 align:middle line:84%
my own psychological emotional
basement to be able to do it.

01:00:04.370 --> 01:00:05.965 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: And you're ready?

01:00:05.965 --> 01:00:07.090 align:middle line:90%
>>CRAMER: Yeah, absolutely.

01:00:07.090 --> 01:00:08.860 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Captain, thanks for
being on "Beyond Belief."

01:00:08.860 --> 01:00:09.160 align:middle line:90%
>>CRAMER: Oh, thank you.

01:00:09.160 --> 01:00:09.680 align:middle line:90%
My pleasure.

01:00:09.680 --> 01:00:10.270 align:middle line:90%
Thanks for having me, George.

01:00:10.270 --> 01:00:10.840 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: I appreciate it.

01:00:10.840 --> 01:00:11.830 align:middle line:90%
>>CRAMER: My pleasure.

01:00:11.830 --> 01:00:14.860 align:middle line:10%
>>NOORY: He says he'll
take a polygraph test

01:00:14.860 --> 01:00:17.210 align:middle line:10%
if offered to him.

01:00:17.210 --> 01:00:18.800 align:middle line:84%
What an amazing
moment that would

01:00:18.800 --> 01:00:22.490 align:middle line:90%
be if he takes it and passes.

01:00:22.490 --> 01:00:26.460 align:middle line:84%
I'm George Noory and thanks
for watching "Beyond Belief."

01:00:26.460 --> 01:00:29.510 align:middle line:90%
